definitions.definition: A country's entire maritime military force, including ships and personnel .
examples: People who get seasick easily shouldn't join the navy .

definitions.definition: A governmental department in charge of a country's maritime military force.
Any fleet of maritime vessels, and especially the entire fleet of any particular nationality , including vessels that are commercial , military , or both.
A dark blue colour , usually called navy blue .

main_definition: ( countable ) A country's entire maritime military force, including ships and personnel .
secondary_definitions: ( countable ) A governmental department in charge of a country's maritime military force.
( archaic , countable ) Any fleet of maritime vessels, and especially the entire fleet of any particular nationality , including vessels that are commercial , military , or both.
( countable and uncountable ) A dark blue colour , usually called navy blue .
